Let me group the terms: = (-i e^(-i7x) +i e^(i7x)) + (7i e^(-i5x) -7i e^(i5x)) + (-21i e^(-i3x) +21i e^(i3x)) + (35i e^(-ix) -35i e^(ix)) Each pair can be written as: For the first pair: -i e^(-i7x) +i e^(i7x) =i ( e^(i7x) - e^(-i7x) ) =i*(2i sin7x)= -2 sin7x Second pair: 7i e^(-i5x) -7i e^(i5x)=7i (e^(-i5x)-e^(i5x))=7i*(-2i sin5x)=7i*(-2i) sin5x=14 sin5x Third pair: -21i e^(-i3x) +21i e^(i3x)=21i (e^(i3x)-e^(-i3x))=21i*(2i sin3x)=42i^2 sin3x=42*(-1) sin3x= -42 sin3x Fourth pair: 35i e^(-ix) -35i e^(ix)=35i (e^(-ix)-e^(ix))=35i*(-2i sinx)= -70i^2 sinx= -70*(-1) sinx=70 sinx Therefore, putting all together: = (-2 sin7x) +14 sin5x + (-42 sin3x) +70 sinx Therefore, sin^7x = (1/128)( -2 sin7x +14 sin5x -42 sin3x +70 sinx ) Simplify the coefficients: Factor out 2 in numerator: = (1/128)*2*(- sin7x +7 sin5x -21 sin3x +35 sinx ) = (1/64)*( - sin7x +7 sin5x -21 sin3x +35 sinx ) Therefore, sin^7x = (35/64) sinx - (21/64) sin3x + (7/64) sin5x - (
